The appellant, SO PING CHI, was the General Manager and Principal Surveyor of Ships in the Marine Department’s Local Vessel Safety Branch (LVSB) from April 2007 to August 2010. His role included enforcing the **Merchant Shipping (Local Vessels) (Safety and Survey) Regulation (Cap 548G)**, which mandated that vessels carry 100% adult lifejackets + 5% children’s lifejackets (up from 40% adult lifejackets with other equipment pre-2007). A 12-month grace period (until January 2008) applied for compliance.  

